<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92 of 15 June 1992 introducing specific measures for the Azores and Madeira relating to certain agricultural products (1), and in particular Articles 23 and 29 (3) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 15. juuni 1992. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1600/92 Assooride ja Madeira suhtes teatavaid p&otilde;llumajandustooteid k&auml;sitlevate erimeetmete rakendamise kohta, eriti selle artiklit 23 ja artikli 29 l&otilde;iget 3, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1676/85 of 11 June 1985 on the value of the unit of account and the conversion rates to be applied for the purposes of the common agricultural policy (2), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2205/90 (3), and in particular Articles 2 (4) and 12 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 11. juuni 1985. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1676/85 arvestus&uuml;hiku v&auml;&auml;rtuse ja &uuml;hises p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitikas rakendatavate &uuml;mberarvestuskursside kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2205/90, eriti selle artikli 2 l&otilde;iget 4 ja artiklit 12, ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 21 of Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92 introduces an aid scheme to support production of Madeira liqueur wines within the limits of the region's traditional requirements; whereas the scheme comprises aid for the purchase of rectified concentrated must produced elsewhere in the Community, aid for the purchase of vinous alcohol obtained from Community distillation operations at a sum determined by tendering procedure and aid for the ageing of liqueur wines paid over three wine years in respect of wines whose ageing period is a minimum of five years and paid each year for a maximum quantity of 20 000 hectolitres; whereas the necessary detailed rules of application should be adopted; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1600/92 artikliga 21 kehtestatakse toetuskava Madeira lik&ouml;&ouml;rveinide tootmise toetamiseks selle piirkonna tavap&auml;rastele valmistusviisidele vastavate vajaduste piires; see kava h&otilde;lmab toetust mujal &uuml;henduse toodetud puhastatud kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirde ostmiseks, toetust &uuml;henduses destilleerimisel saadud veinialkoholi ostmiseks pakkumismenetlusel m&auml;&auml;ratud hinnaga ja toetust lik&ouml;&ouml;rveinide laagerdamiseks, mida makstakse kolme veiniaasta jooksul veinide suhtes, mille laagerdusaeg on v&auml;hemalt viis aastat, ja mida makstakse igal aastal k&otilde;ige rohkem 20 000-hektoliitrise koguse suhtes; selle kava kohaldamiseks tuleks vastu v&otilde;tta vajalikud &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to supply Madeira with vinous alcohol; the conditions for tendering for the supply operation should be defined; whereas the tendering cover the determination of the price for purchasing alcohol obtained from Community distillation operations under conditions which do not disturb the Community market in alcohol and spirit drinks and should cover delivery to Madeira; whereas provision should be made to guarantee that the product is indeed used to produce liqueur wines in Madeira; </inglise>
<eesti> Madeira varustamiseks veinialkoholiga tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata tarnimiseks korraldatava pakkumise tingimused; pakkumine h&otilde;lmab &uuml;henduses destilleerimisel saadud alkoholi ostuhinna kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramist sellistel tingimustel, mis ei h&auml;iri &uuml;henduse alkoholi- ja piiritusjoogituru toimimist, ning nimetatud toote tarnimist Madeirale; tuleks tagada, et k&otilde;nealust toodet kasutatakse t&otilde;epoolest lik&ouml;&ouml;rveinide valmistamiseks Madeiral; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to ensure that the aid scheme for the ageing of liqueur wines can be administered in a proper and uncomplicated manner, contracts should be concluded between the interested producers and the competent agency in Madeira for ageing the wine for at least five years; whereas, in the same spirit, payment of the aid should be distributed equally over the contract period and made contingent on the lodging on a one-off performance security for a reasonable sum; </inglise>
<eesti> lik&ouml;&ouml;rveinide laagerdamise toetuskava n&otilde;uetekohase ja t&otilde;rgeteta haldamise tagamiseks tuleks huvitatud tootjate ja Madeira p&auml;deva asutuse vahel s&otilde;lmida v&auml;hemalt viieaastased veinilaagerdamislepingud; lisaks sellele tuleks toetust maksta lepingu kehtivusaja l&otilde;ikes v&otilde;rdeliselt ja seada tingimuseks &uuml;hekordse t&auml;itmistagatise esitamine m&otilde;istliku summa ulatuses; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Articles 22 and 29 of Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92 introduce a per hectare aid scheme in the Azores and Madeira for the continued cultivation of vines for the production of quality wines psr in traditional production zones; whereas the detailed rules needed to administer the scheme and to ensure monitoring of the conditions adopted by the Council should be laid down; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1600/92 artiklitega 22 ja 29 kehtestatakse Assooride ja Madeira tavap&auml;rastes tootmispiirkondades mpv-kvaliteetveinide valmistamiseks kasutatavate viinamarjasortide kasvatamise alalhoidmiseks hektaritoetuste kava; tuleks ette n&auml;ha selle kava haldamise ja n&otilde;ukogu s&auml;testatud tingimuste t&auml;itmise kontrollimise &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the rates to be used to convert into national currency the amounts fixed pursuant to the above aid schemes should be determined; whereas, in order to avoid the risk of monetary distortion, the rate to be used should be closer to economic reality than the agricultural conversion rate while respecting application of the correcting factor referred to in Article 2 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 1676/86; whereas Article 3a of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3152/85 (4), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 3237/90 (5), laying down detailed rules for the application of Regulation (EEC) No 1676/85, provides for the publication of such a rate; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata kursid, mida kasutada eespool nimetatud toetuskavade alusel kehtestatud summade &uuml;mberarvestamisel omav&auml;&auml;ringusse; v&auml;ltimaks v&auml;&auml;ringutest tingitud moonutuste ohtu, peaks kasutatava kursi puhul arvestama tegelikku majandusolukorda rohkem kui p&otilde;llumajandusliku &uuml;mberarvestuskursi puhul, kohaldades samas m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1676/85 artikli 2 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud paranduskoefitsienti; komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr. 3152/85, millega kehtestatakse &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1676/85 kohaldamiseks, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr. 3237/90, artikliga 3a n&auml;hakse ette selle kursi avaldamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for by Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92 are applicable from 1 July 1992; whereas the detailed rules in this Regulation should be applicable from that date; </inglise>
